_Remark_: https://github.com/libgdx/libgdx/pull/1292 fixes this issue.

_On_: Github master branch, 1.0-SNAPSHOT (04-02-'14), d8ed37451277ec075b2118dff

_Error_:
Enums which implement behaviour specified in the base enum; thus resulting in anonymous innerclasses being created, don't de-serialize properly.

Testcase that showcases crash up de-serialization:

``` java
public class EnumSerialization {

    public static class TestClass {

        public enum Test {
            A() {

                @Override
                public void doIt () {
                    System.out.println("TEST");
                }

            };

            public abstract void doIt ();
        }

        protected Test a;

        public TestClass () {
        }

        public TestClass (Test a) {
            this.a = a;
        }
    }

    @Test
    public void test () {

        Json json = new Json();
        TestClass test = new TestClass(TestClass.Test.A);

        String jsonString = json.prettyPrint(test);

        System.out.println(jsonString);

        TestClass testC = json.fromJson(TestClass.class, jsonString);

    }

}
```

If you use constructor with positioning like:
new Sprite(texture, x, y, sizeX, sizeY);
x and y still zero.

I have a scene which requires some assets to be loaded. During the scene change the new scene FIRST require their resources first and THEN the old scene release its resources.

This is done to prevent the same resource to unload from the old scene and then immediately to load it again. Reference counting of assetManager works well here. All works except that progress value (actually toLoad value) becomes wrong.

What steps will reproduce the problem?
    assetManager.load("themes/hero.g3db", Model.class);
    assetManager.finishLoading();
    assetManager.load("themes/hero.g3db", Model.class);
    assetManager.unload("themes/hero.g3db");
    assetManager.finishLoading();
    float progress = assetManager.getProgress();

What is the expected output?
    progress is expected to be 1f
    internally assetManager.toLoad expected to be 0

Actually got:
    progress is 0f (but the loading is completely finished);
    internally assetManager.toLoad is 1 (but there is nothing to load)

What version of libgdx are you using?
    latest nightly

assetManager.load method has this:
    if (loadQueue.size == 0) {
        loaded = 0;
        toLoad = 0;
    }

Either a similar thing should be added to assetManager.progress method, or toLoad-- should be present in assetManager.unload when resource is unload from queue (probably also from tasks?)
